    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Although the model manages to generate music with good quality and structure, it is still far from perfect.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content7 cid-ttbhFZC4Ql" id="content7-8" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
        <div class="container"><div class="row justify-content-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-9"><blockquote><p class="ff4">First, since Museformer takes random samplings during inference and does not receive manual control, it can hardly ensure that every generated music piece is well-structured in an expected way. Techniques to enhance its reliability and controllability can be further explored. Furthermore, the musicality and creativity of the generated music are still far behind that of human-made music, which remains a problem for all the existing music generation models.</p></blockquote></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Here you can listen to some of the musical examples that have been created:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><div class="sketchy"><a href="https://ai-muzic.github.io/museformer/"><h2 style="color:blueviolet; font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:25px;">Museformer: Transformer with Fine- and Coarse-Grained Attention for Music Generation</h2><h3 style="color:rgb(45, 34, 54); font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:20px;">Corresponding author. Symbolic music generation aims to generate music scores automatically. A recent trend is to use…</h3><p>ai-muzic.github.io</p></a></div></div></div></div></section><br><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In addition, Museformer is part of a larger project by Microsoft. the project called Muzic (<a href="https://github.com/microsoft/muzic" target="_self">GitHub repository here</a>).</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
